data.text: @SDECoxHealth Question: that second picture is not from the WTCCU (“new” Covid unit”), but rather the elevator lobby of the old SDU that was being used for Covid pts (the 540’s). Did that unit close too? Is there a dedicated unit anymore?
@vocologist @SDECoxHealth I could tell you what helped me and my entire family sail through Covid, but I would probably get blocked. Just know this: viable treatments are out there 😉
@SDECoxHealth And may it never have a need to reopen as an emergency use facility.

@aprilg640 @SDECoxHealth Cool! That's really refreshing to hear. Some days I feel like the only person in SGF that takes this pandemic seriously! Other than Steve, of course! (But he gets paid to take it seriously, right? Joking!)
@KnightlyLeslie @SDECoxHealth @vocologist Paxlovid can’t be taken with many immunosuppressants. Not an option for a lot of at risk people.
@SDECoxHealth My prayer is that it will never have to open again.
@SDECoxHealth Finally!! God bless all of the Hero's of Cox Health!!!🙏😇✝️

@SDECoxHealth @sgfbeerbuzz This part of society was happy to wear a mask. Stopped at work awhile back, but continued when going to a store. Two years I wasn't sick. Last Tuesday an I'll coworker was in my space. He is sick and now I am too. Not covid.
